Create an instance in a Public subnet and a database in a Private subnet.
Remember to have a security group that allows the following ports HTTP (80), HTTPS (443), SSH {(22) & your IP only} 
and Aurora SQL (3306) attached to your instance and a security group that allows SSH {(22) & your IP address only} 
and Aurora SQL {(3306) & your CIDR block address} attached to your database.
After making sure both are running, now you need to SSH or direct connect to your database from your instance.
For example you can SSH using Putty or Mobaxterm, follow the prompts and once you it displays your welcome message
the following steps should be used:
